      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "On headless Linux servers running CI or cloud agent workloads, start a virtual framebuffer before importing pyautogui:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Start a virtual display at 1280x800 on display :99\nXvfb :99 -screen 0 1280x800x24 &\nexport DISPLAY=:99\n\n# Now pyautogui and PIL.ImageGrab work normally\npython3 agent.py"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "pyvirtualdisplay"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " package wraps Xvfb and lets you start and stop it from Python:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from pyvirtualdisplay import Display\n\ndef run_agent_headless(task: str) -> str:\n    with Display(visible=False, size=(1280, 800)) as _display:\n        # Any pyautogui / PIL calls inside here use the virtual display\n        return run_agent(task)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Common Pitfalls"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Clicking outside the window."
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " The model returns coordinates relative to the screenshot, but the window may be partially off-screen or at a different DPI scale. Verify coordinates are within "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "(0, 0, screen_width, screen_height)"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " before clicking."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "High-DPI displays."
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " On Retina/HiDPI displays, the logical resolution (what pyautogui uses) is half the physical pixel count. PIL.ImageGrab captures at physical resolution. Divide captured coordinates by the DPI scale factor before clicking."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "typewrite drops non-ASCII silently."
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " Always use the clipboard path ("
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "pyperclip.copy + Ctrl+V"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ") for user-supplied text that may contain accented characters, emoji, or CJK."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Focus not on target window."
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " Clicking coordinates that belong to a background window does nothing visible until the window is brought to front. Click once to focus, wait for the focus animation, then perform the intended action."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Scroll direction varies by OS."
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "pyautogui.scroll(3)"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " scrolls "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "italic"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "up"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " on macOS (natural scrolling) and "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "italic"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "down"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " on Windows. Normalise by asking the model which direction moved content toward the target element."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Mouse and keyboard control translate the vision model's element identification into real desktop interactions. pyautogui provides all the primitives: smooth mouse movement, single and double clicks, drag, scroll, typewrite for ASCII, hotkey for shortcuts, and clipboard-based paste for Unicode. Wrap these behind a typed action schema so the agent loop stays clean and the input layer is fully testable with mocks. Always enable FAILSAFE, add inter-action pauses for slow UIs, and wait for screen stability after any action that triggers navigation or animation."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}